title: Find a lost National Insurance number

heading_context: Find a lost National Insurance number
chunks.html_content:
If you do not know your National Insurance number, the quickest and easiest way to find it is:

  • online through your personal tax account
  • in the HMRC app
  • in your Apple or Google Wallet (if you previously saved it there from your personal tax account)
  • on a document you already have, for example a payslip or P60

If you need a letter that shows your National Insurance number, you can print one from your personal tax account or the app.

heading_context: Find a lost National Insurance number
chunks.html_content: HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) will not tell you your National Insurance number over the phone. If you call them, it can take up to 15 days to get a letter with your National Insurance number.

chunks.html_content:
You may be able to find it on your:

  • payslip
  • P60
  • letters about tax, pensions or benefits

heading_context: Find a lost National Insurance number
Ask HMRC for your National Insurance number
chunks.html_content:
If you still cannot find it, you can:

  • fill in form CA5403 and send it to the address on the form
  • contact the National Insurance numbers helpline and answer some questions (you’ll need to fill in form CA5403 if you cannot answer the questions)

HMRC will post it to you and it will arrive within 15 working days.

HMRC no longer sends out National Insurance cards.
